3.6 Mechanical Integrity - A!A?68.73   

The following process equipment is included in the PAPCO mechanical integrity program.

(1) Pressure vessels and storage tanks;

(2) Piping systems (including piping components such as valves);

(3) Relief and vent systems and devices;

(4) Emergency shutdown systems;

(5) Controls (including monitoring devices and sensors, alarms, and interlocks) and,

(6) Pumps.

PAPCO has established and implemented written procedures to maintain the on-going integrity of process equipment.  PAPCO trains each employee involved in maintaining the on-going integrity of process equipment.  The training provides an overview of each process, its hazards, and procedures applicable to the employee's job tasks.

Inspections and tests are performed on the regulated process equipment.   Inspection and testing procedures follow recognized and generally accepted good engineering practices.  The frequency of inspections and tests of process equipment is consistent with applicable manufacturers' recommendations and good engineering practices, and more frequently if determined to be necessary by prior operating experience.  In addition to the required inspection recommendations, PAPCO employees perform daily walkthroughs at the facility in order to identify potential hazards or concerns.  

